Peter Jennings, the face of ABC News for 40 years, has been diagnosed with lung cancer.
Despite his illness, he plans to continue anchoring "World News Tonight" during chemotherapy.
Jennings, along with Dan Rather and Tom Brokaw, once dominated network news.
However, the rise of cable TV and the Internet has shifted viewer preferences.
Jennings' battle with cancer has raised concerns about the future of network anchors.
ABC News is preparing for his absence by using substitute anchors.
Jennings' personal battle with cancer has touched viewers and colleagues alike, showcasing his courage and strength.
